## 2. pgas ⇄ consumer communication protocol (READ + RUN EVERY CYCLE)

This repo's autonomous loop coordinates with the pgas curator
**ENTIRELY** via GitHub. Full spec: `simodelne/pgas` →
`CONSUMER-COMMS-PROTOCOL.md`. Run all four channels once per working
cycle (and at least every ~30 min while active).

### Channel 1 — Version alignment (this consumer self-service, EVERY cycle)

Check the latest published pgas version and bump if behind:

```bash
LATEST=$(NPM_TOKEN=$(gh auth token) npm view @simodelne/pgas-runtime version \
  --registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com)
```

If your pinned `@simodelne/pgas-*` range is behind `$LATEST`:

1. Read pgas release notes + `docs/prompt-migration-*.md` for breaking
   changes (pgas tags breaking vs non-breaking in `HANDOVER.md`).
2. Bump **all** `@simodelne/pgas-*` deps to `^$LATEST`, refresh the
   lockfile, run typecheck + tests.
3. Open PR titled `chore(deps): align to pgas v$LATEST`. Merge once
   gates are green. (pgas publishes the 10 packages in lockstep;
   `^x.y.z` resolves all.)

Non-breaking bumps need no curator sign-off. A **breaking** bump waits
for the corresponding migration broadcast (Channel 2).

**This consumer is pinned to `{{ENGINE_VERSION}}` at scaffold time.**
Update as the engine evolves; track via this channel.

### Channel 2 — Broadcasts (curator → ALL consumers)

```bash
gh issue list --repo simodelne/pgas --state open --label consumer-broadcast \
  --json number,title,body,createdAt
```

For each open broadcast that applies: act on it, then **ACK** by
commenting on the broadcast issue:

```
<<<ack:simodelne/{{CONSUMER_NAME}}>>>
<one-line status: done / in-progress / n/a-because-X>
```

### Channel 3 — Ad-hoc messages (curator → THIS consumer)

```bash
gh issue list --repo simodelne/{{CONSUMER_NAME}} --state open --label pgas-curator \
  --json number,title,body,comments
```

Body opens with `<<<from-pgas-curator>>>`. Address each, respond by
comment (prefix `<<<from-{{CONSUMER_NAME}}>>>`), close when resolved.

### Channel 4 — Update requests (THIS consumer → curator/pgas)

When you need an engine/server change in pgas, **file an issue on
`simodelne/pgas`** — do NOT work around a pgas gap with a local hack.

- **Title:** `[{{CONSUMER_NAME}}-ask] <one-line summary>`
- **Label:** `consumer-request`
- **Body:** open with `<<<from-{{CONSUMER_NAME}}-orchestrator-session>>>`, then the
  **data-driven format**: `Observed` (exact log line / error /
  registry output), `Inferred (given X)`, minimal `Reproduction`,
  `Blocking what`, `What I've tried` (consumer-side), `Acceptance check`.
- **Urgency:** `[BLOCKING]` / `[P1]` / `[NICE_TO_HAVE]`.

