## 4. FM-closure discipline (pgas#253)

The plugin scaffold closes the five failure modes from
[pgas#253](https://github.com/simodelne/pgas/issues/253) by
construction. Every PR must keep them closed:

| FM | What it is | Where the scaffold closes it |
|----|------------|-------------------------------|
| FM1 | Handlers read action payload only; engine stores flat-key domain | `programs/*/handlers/_resolver.ts` |
| FM2 | `InnerContinuationReplay` + `SessionLockExhausted` consumers not wired | `server/index.ts` (registers both) |
| FM3 | `system_mode_entry` admission too broad under v1.8.x | `programs/*/spec.yml` (admits only on bootstrap modes) |
| FM4 | Handler-backed raw tool with no `createAdapters` override silently `undefined`s | Documented in `programs/*/README.md` |
| FM5 | Engine-owned `inputs.query_meta.*` paths not in consumer schema | `programs/*/spec.yml` (schema includes them) |

Every PR runs `/pgas:5-fm-audit` in CI. A FAIL blocks merge.

When cutting a major or minor version, run `/pgas:architecture-doc` to
generate `audit/ARCHITECTURE-{{CONSUMER_NAME}}-v<X.Y.0>.md` per
[`CONSUMER-VERSIONING-CONTRACT.md`](https://github.com/simodelne/pgas/blob/main/CONSUMER-VERSIONING-CONTRACT.md)
§ 1. The plugin's `post-tool-use-arch-doc-nudge.sh` hook reminds you
on `npm publish` of a `.0` version.

