## 5. Agent behavior — orchestrator role

Per `simodelne/pgas`/CLAUDE.md "Agent behavior — classifier denials
and orchestration", this repo runs the orchestrator + sub-agents model.

| Role | Who | Responsibilities |
|------|-----|------------------|
| **Orchestrator** | Main Claude session | Defines scope + acceptance criteria, dispatches briefs, reviews PRs, validates CI, merges. NEVER writes code directly (except pure GH metadata) |
| **Sub-agent** | `Agent`-tool dispatched | Writes code + tests, opens a PR with the brief verbatim in `## Brief`, returns a short report. NEVER self-merges |
| **Curator** (human) | `{{GH_OWNER}}` | Final veto on behavioral surfaces via CODEOWNERS |

Operational rules:

1. Bug reports → GitHub Issues (`bug.yml` template).
2. Improvement requests → GitHub Issues (`improvement.yml`).
3. Sub-agent briefs are reproducible — paste verbatim in `## Brief`.
4. No sub-agent self-merges (CODEOWNERS + branch protection).
5. Acceptance criteria precede implementation.

